chat_history: MIGUEL: I have a dimple on this side, but not on this side. Dimple. No dimple. Dimple. No dimple--
Narrator: Miguel's ABUELITA (70s) runs the table like a ship captain. She gives Mama Coco a kiss on the head.
MIGUEL: My Abuelita? She's Mama Coco's daughter.
Narrator: Abuelita piles extra tamales on Miguel's plate.
ABUELITA: Aw, you're a twig, mijo. Have some more.
ABUELITA: I asked if you would like more tamales.
ABUELITA: That's what I THOUGHT you said.
MIGUEL: Abuelita runs our house just like Mama Imelda did.
